{
    "title": "Position",
    "ref": "position",
    "contents": [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "parts": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "In physics, the "
                },
                {
                    "type": "bold",
                    "value": "position"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " of, say, a body or particle, refers to a quantification of its "
                },
                {
                    "type": "italic",
                    "value": "location in space"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", usually with respect some chosen origin (which, loosely speaking, has position zero)."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "parts": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "Depending on the system, one includes one or several number of "
                },
                {
                    "type": "italic",
                    "value": "components"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " of the position, referred to as "
                },
                {
                    "type": "bold",
                    "value": "coordinates"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ". In a system wehere all three spatial components are needed for a description, they are usually denoted "
                },
                {
                    "type": "latex",
                    "value": "x, y, z"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "parts": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "In quantum mechanics, the position coordinates are considered as operators acting on state vectors of a system. It is of immense importance in "
                },
                {
                    "type": "ref",
                    "value": "wave-mechanics",
                    "label": "wave mechanics"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", which generally describes the states of a system in terms of wave functions, which are then functions of the position (see the page on "
                },
                {
                    "type": "ref",
                    "value": "schrodinger-representation",
                    "label": "Schr√∂dinger representation"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ")."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}